sections.Biography:
===Background===
Rhaenyra was a Princess of the [[House Targaryen|Targaryen dynasty]]. She was the half-sister of [[Aegon II Targaryen]], and the mother of future king [[Aegon III Targaryen]]. Her son Aegon III was himself the father of Kings [[Daeron I Targaryen]] and [[Baelor Targaryen]].

Rhaenyra fought her brother Aegon II for the [[Iron Throne]] in a civil war of succession known as the [[Dance of the Dragons]]. She eventually was defeated and Aegon II had his [[dragon]] devour her.&lt;ref&gt;[[The Death of Kings]]&lt;/ref&gt;

===[[Season 3]]===

[[File:Ambush at Dragonstone.png|thumb|left|Rhaenyra is eaten by [[Sunfyre]]]]Touring the [[Great Sept of Baelor]] in [[King's Landing]], King [[Joffrey Baratheon]] explains to [[Margaery Tyrell]] the fate of Rhaenyra Targaryen. Joffrey points out the crypts where what little is left of her is kept.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[And Now His Watch is Ended]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;
